{
  "answer": "**The Viṣṇu Smṛti does not contain a dedicated chapter that specifically lays out the duties of a *snātaka* (Vedic graduate, who has completed the *brahmacarya* or studentship stage).**\n\nSearches for \"snataka\", \"snātaka\", \"graduate\", \"Vedic graduate\", \"bathed\", \"studentship\", and related terms across the text yielded no such section. The early chapters cover topics like creation myths (Ch. 1), *varṇa* duties (Ch. 2), royal duties (Ch. 3), measurements (Ch. 4), and punishments (Ch. 5), but do not detail *āśrama* (*āśrama*, life-stage) duties.[^1][^2][^3][^4][^5]\n\nThe term \"Vedic graduate\" (rendering *snātaka*) appears incidentally elsewhere:\n- Chapter 54, on penances, references violation of a Vedic graduate's vows.[^6]\n- Chapter 63, on travel etiquette, requires yielding the path to a Vedic graduate (among others).[^7]\n\nDetailed *snātaka* rules (e.g., conduct after studentship) appear in other Smṛtis like the *Manusmṛti* (Ch. 4), but not here.[^8]\n\n[^1]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 1](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/01/translation/).\n[^2]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 2](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/02/translation/).\n[^3]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 3](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/03/translation/).\n[^4]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 4](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/04/translation/).\n[^5]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 5](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/05/translation/).\n[^6]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 54](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/54/translation/#p-b202b7).\n[^7]: Viṣṇu Smṛti, [Chapter 63](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/63/translation/#p-0b5003).\n[^8]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 4 (not in Viṣṇu Smṛti).",
